reason.tex:
%text Let us prove one result \[ \qquad \sin^{-1}\frac{1}{x} = \csc^{-1} x\] and then perhaps you can work out the others
% \begin{align} \csc\theta &= x \implies \frac{1}{\sin\theta} =x \\ \therefore \sin\theta &= \frac{1}{x} \implies \theta = \sin^{-1}\frac{1}{x} \\ \text{But }\theta &= \csc^{-1} x \\ \therefore \csc^{-1}x &= \sin^{-1}\frac{1}{x} \end{align} %text
Similarly % \begin{align} \sec^{-1} x &= \cos^{-1}\frac{1}{x} \\ \cot^{-1} x &= \tan^{-1}\frac{1}{x} \quad (x\gt 0) \\ &= -\pi + \cot^{-1} x \quad (x\lt 0) \end{align}
